excerpt: Remains of an 11th-century fort & military post on a hill, built by the 37th Gond ruler.
detail_description: Madan Mahal Fort is an 11th-century fort and military post located on a hill, built by the 37th Gond ruler. It is one of the major tourist attractions in Jabalpur, offering panoramic views of the city. The fort was historically the residence of Gond queen Rani Durgavati and features standard architectural elements along with unique passageways, underground routes, and sharp turns.
name: Madan Mahal Fort
address: Gurudev Colony, Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh 482001, India

excerpt: This roadside rock formation is comprised of a big oval stone steadied over another large stone.
detail_description: Balancing Rock in Jabalpur is a stunning natural wonder where a large oval stone appears to be delicately balanced on another massive rock. This geological formation has defied the forces of nature, remaining intact despite storms, rain, and seasonal erosion. It even withstood a powerful 6.9 magnitude earthquake without being disturbed.
name: Balancing Rock
address: 4WX3+9XF, Ratan Nagar, Madan Mahal, Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh 482001, India

excerpt: Traditional museum housing history displays, prehistoric objects & sculptural artworks.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Jabalpur, the Rani Durgavati Museum is a captivating destination for history buffs and culture enthusiasts alike. This museum pays homage to the brave Gond queen, Rani Durgavati, who valiantly defended her kingdom against Mughal invaders. Visitors can immerse themselves in an extensive collection of artifacts, coins, paintings, and sculptures that span various historical periods. The exhibits not only celebrate her legendary exploits but also provide insights into her strategic brilliance during battles.
name: Rani Durgavati Museum
